===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|arrayen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|arayer|lang=xno}} (compare {{etyl|fro|-}} {{term|arayer|lang=fro}}, {{term|areer||to put in order|lang=fro}}), from {{etyl|ML.}} {{term|arredo|arrēdō|to put in order, arrange, array|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|ML.}} *{{term||rēdum|preparation, order|lang=la}}, of {{etyl|gem}} origin, from {{etyl|frk}} *{{term||reida|preparation, order|lang=frk}} or {{etyl|got}} {{term|𐌲𐌰𐍂𐌰𐌹𐌳𐍃||tr=garaids|ready, prepared|lang=got}}, from {{proto|Germanic|raidaz||raidiz|ready|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|reidʰ-|to put in order, ease, make comfortable|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|gireiti|gireiti|preparation|lang=goh}}, {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|rede|rēde|ready|lang=ofs}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|geræde|ġerǣde|preparation, equipment|lang=ang}}. More at [[ready]].

